{"lemma":"عاج","slug":"عاج","root":"ع.#.ج","root_slug":"ع-_-ج","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-_-ج","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun_prop","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n28088","n28089","n30917"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D8%A7%D8%AC"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ivory"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From عَوِجَ (ʕawija, “to be crooked, to be bent”)."},"ipa":["[ʕæːd͡ʒ]"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n28088","headword_ar":"عَاجِ","root":"Ej","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAj~a","text_ar":"عَاجَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A cry by which a she-camel is chidden."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K.) [But the former belongs to art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ewj","text_ar":"عوج"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.]"}],"source_refs":["S","K","L"]},{"entry_id":"n28089","headword_ar":"عَاجٌّ","root":"Ej","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[part. n. of 1], applied to a road, [app. because a crowded road is usually noisy,] means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Full."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K.) [Compare"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaj~aAjN","text_ar":"عَجَّاجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a river.]"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n30917","headword_ar":"عَاجٌ","root":"Ewj","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", as an epithet applied to a she-camel,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Pliable;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lay~inapN AlA^aEoTaAfi","text_ar":"لَيِّنَةٌ الاَعْطَافِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lay~inapu AlAinoEiTaAfi","text_ar":"لَيِّنَةُ الاِنْعِطَافِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to different copies of the K; and by the latter words is expl. (but not in the K) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAy^ijapN","text_ar":"عَايِجَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", as so applied: in the L,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAjN","text_ar":"عَاجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is expl. as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tractable, submissive,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manageable;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mi*oEaAnN","text_ar":"مِذْعَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mi*oEaAnu Als~ayori lay~inapu AlAinoEiTaAfi","text_ar":"مِذْعَانُ السَّيْرِ لَيِّنَةُ الاِنْعِطَافِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(thus in the O:) and it is said to be without a parallel in respect of the dropping of the [fem. termination]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", whether its original measure be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEilN","text_ar":"فَعِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAEilN","text_ar":"فَاعِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[?]. (TA.)       -A2-  Also ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ivory;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"elephant's bone;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K;) or [rather] only"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"elephant's tusk;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, Msb, TA;) thus say ISd and Kz: (TA:) n. un. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a piece of ivory"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, O:) of its properties are these: that if seed-produce or trees be fumigated with it, worms will not approach them; and the woman who drinks of it every day two drachms with water and honey, if compressed after seven days, conceives. (K.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Tortoise-shell;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*abolN","text_ar":"ذَبْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]; (O, K;) i. e. (O) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"back"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shell"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the sea-tortoise"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"turtle"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (O, Msb:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masakN","text_ar":"مَسَكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Sh, L:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing that is made from the back of the sea-tortoise:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:) and it is said that the Arabs called"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sort of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bone"},{"kind":"text","text":"by this name: n. un. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) The Prophet is related to have had a comb of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EAj","text_ar":"عاج"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*abol","text_ar":"ذَبْل"},{"kind":"text","text":": (L:) and he is said to have ordered to purchase for Fátimeh a pair of bracelets of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EAj","text_ar":"عاج"},{"kind":"text","text":", by which he meant not what is turned of elephants' tusks, for their tusks are"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mayotap","text_ar":"مَيْتَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", [i. e. they are taken from an animal of which the flesh is unlawful food,] but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*bl","text_ar":"ذبل"},{"kind":"text","text":": (O, * L, Msb: *) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EAj","text_ar":"عاج"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the elephant is impure accord. to EshSháfi'ee, but pure accord. to Aboo-Haneefeh. (L.) ―         -b3-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Bracelets of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EAj","text_ar":"عاج"},{"kind":"text","text":", as distinguished from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*abol","text_ar":"ذَبْل"},{"kind":"text","text":", [i. e. of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ivory:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and probably of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tortoise-shell"},{"kind":"text","text":"also:] (ISh:) n. un. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jwj","text_ar":"جوج"},{"kind":"text","text":".)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAji","text_ar":"عَاجِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, L, K,) indecl., with kesr for its termination, (L, K,) as a determinate noun; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAjK","text_ar":"عَاجٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with tenween, as an indeterminate noun; (L;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A cry by which a she-camel is chidden:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, L, K:) Az says, in chiding a she-camel, one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAji","text_ar":"عَاجِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", without tenween; and if he please,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAjo","text_ar":"عَاجْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with jezm, as though a pause were imagined to be made after it: or, accord. to A'Obeyd, one says to her"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAjK","text_ar":"عَاجٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAhK","text_ar":"جَاهٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with tenween: [but see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jwh","text_ar":"جوه"},{"kind":"text","text":":] accord. to AHeyth, a word of this kind is originally mejzoom; but in the case of a rhyme, [and in any case of poetical necessity,] it may be makhfood. (TA.) [See also art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ej","text_ar":"عج"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["TA","S","O","Msb","Sh","L","ISh","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}